Metric: Recent Order Revenue (SQLite)
Description: Revenue from completed orders in the last 7 days, pulled from an app's local SQLite database. The pattern for trust-checking an application DB directly — no ETL required.
Owner: demo
Tags: demo, sqlite, revenue

Source: orders

Given all records from the orders table
  And status is "completed"
  And amount is present
  And order_date is within the last 7 days

When we calculate
  Then sum the amount column across qualifying orders
  And round to 2 decimal places

The result is "Recent Order Revenue"

Trust:
  Freshness must be less than 24 hours
  Null rate on amount must be less than 5%
  Null rate on order_id must be 0%
  Value must be between 100 and 1000000
